@NODE "browser" "browser"
--------------------
THE BROWSER WINDOW
--------------------

On top of the main window of ShowGUI you will see some
buttons (the button-images are located in the images-
drawer  and you can change them of course!).

OPEN

Load a picture into the main window of ShowGUI

SAVE

Save the picture to a different location

COPY

Copy the picture to your favourite location on your HD.
You have to set the path for this location first. This can
be done via the config!

EDIT

You can edit the picture with any paint program. Just
give ShowGUi the path+filename of your favourite
paint proggy and next time you click on edit, the pic
will be loaded into the one, you selected. Configure
the paint programm path via the config!

SHOW EX

This shows the same pic with an alternative viewer.
Don't forget to define your favourite viewer via the 
config first.

CONFIG

See @{"config" LINK "config"}

ABOUT

Some infos and a mad picture of me...:)

QUIT

Makes a toast for you :)

BOOKMARKS

Click on this button to open the bookmark
list. See @{"piclist" LINK "piclist"}

For the menus, read the @{"menus" LINK "menus"}-section!

There is also a string field, in which you can directly enter the
path+filename for a picture. Then click on SHOW (next to the
string gadget) and it will be displayed in the main window.
This is of good use, if you have lots of pictures, called 1.jpg,
2.jpg, 3.jpg, etc..it's much faster to replace this manually than
having to wait for the filerequester to open again.;)

@ENDNODE
@NODE "menus" "menus"
------
MENUS
------
ShowGUI doesn't have many menu items...

SHOWGUI

Here you can load and save a picture, iconify
ShowGUI or can have a look at the ABOUT 
window, if you like ;)

MANAGEMENT

Here you can copy a picture to a different
location. A file requester will appear and
you just select a dir and the pic will be
copied there...easy, isn't it?

DELETE

If you browse your pictures and want to
delete the current one or others, select
this option. It will open a file requester.
If you select OK, the current picture will
be deleted (There's a requester asking
you before deleting, by the way). If you
want to delete another picture (which is
not currently shown in the main window)
you just select it and it will be deleted also.

LHA ADD

You can turn your pic into an LHA archive
with this option. But you'll need LHA located
in your C: directory! If it's not there, ShowGUI
will tell so with a req. A filerequester will open
and you just select a path and a filename. A
shell window will open telling you the LHA progress.




@ENDNODE
@NODE "config" "config"
-------
CONFIG
-------

PICTURE PATH

Choose your favourite path for showing pictures here.

COPY PATH

If you select COPY from the MAIN WINDOW, the current 
picture will be copied to this path.

PROGGY PATH

This is for defining a paint program. Enter path+filename 
of the paint proggy here. Next time you click on EDIT in 
the MAIN WINDOW, the current picture will be loaded
into your defined paint program.

GUI PATTERN

Here you can select a background pattern/picture
for most of the ShowGUI windows. Don't forget
to checkmark USE PATTERN to activate it.

SELECT VIEWER

Here you can select an external viewer and can
also provide some arguments, if needed. For example,
if you choose 'Visage' with some arguments, like
COLOR=BEST, you can click on VIEW EXT in the MAIN
WINDOW of ShowGUI and the pic will be also shown 
by Visage in this case...

ARGUMENTS

See VIEWER

LOAD LAST PIC ON STARTUP

If checked, the last loaded picture will be loaded again on 
next startup - so you can always find out, which location
you have been browing last time. So you can continue there 
again for bookmarks, etc.
If not, only the ShowGUI-logo will be show on next startup.

USE PATTERN

If you check this, the selected pattern will be used, otherwise
ShowGUI loads in a default, neutral and grey background, 
which is located in the 'images' drawer.

To save your settings, select SAVE...otherwise select OK!
@ENDNODE
@NODE "piclist" "piclist"
-------
PICLIST
-------
If you click on BOOKMARKS in the MAIN WINDOW of ShowGUI,
a listview will open, containing your piclists/bookmarks:

SHOW

Shows you the currently highlighted pic of the bookmark list
in the MAIN WINDOW of ShowGUI. This way it is very easy
to browse through lots of pictures.

LOAD

Loads a bookmark list into the listview

SAVE

Saves the listview over the old one

SAVE AS

Save the listview with a different name

SAVE DEF.

Saves the bookmark list as default. So next time you start 
ShowGUI it will be loaded in automatically.

ADD

Adds one or more pictures to the bookmark list. A filereq
will open. Just select one or more pictures there.


BOOKMARK

Adds a pic, which has already been loaded from the 
MAIN WINDOW of ShowGUI  to the current bookmark list.
It simply takes the currently shown picture into the
currently shown bookmark list :)

CONFIG

See @{"pconfig" LINK "pconfig"}!

EDIT

Here you can edit the current entry of the bookmark
list. You can alter name, artist, date and type here.
If you want to edit a new entry just click on another
one from the list and the edit-window will be updated
automatically.

DELETE

Deletes a bookmark entry from the list.

CLEAR

Deletes the whole list

VIEW EXT

Here you can define a SECOND viewer for showing the pics with 
an external viewer like MysticView, Visage, Multiview, etc...
Select the viewer via the @{"pconfig" LINK "pconfig"}!

@ENDNODE
@NODE "pconfig" "pconfig"
-------------
PICLIST CONFIG
-------------

CHOOSE VIEWER

Choose an external viewer here, like Mystic
View, Multiview, Visage, etc...You need to select
both the path and the filename of the viewer.

ARGUMENTS

Here you can add some arguments for the
viewer. For example, you could write:
MODE=DBLPal COLOR=BEST for Visage.

PICLIST PATH

The path, where you have your bookmark lists.

ARTIST DEFAULT

The default for the artist if the pics. You can
use it if you only want to bookmark pics, you have
drawn yourself. So you don't have to type
in your name again and again...good for lazy
people ;)

TYPE DEFAULT

Enter a format default here, like JPG, PNG, IFF, etc

DATE DEFAULT

The default date.

Press SAVE to save your settings,  OK to use them
only. HELP provides some extra info. (For those, who
are too lazy for reading this guide! By the way: Thanx
for reading! ;)
 

@ENDNODE
@NODE "tips" "tips"
----
TIPS
----

HOW TO SNAPSHOT WINDOWS
--------------------------
To snapshot the windows of ShowGUI press CTRL + G and
select SAVE!

SCROLLING PICTURES
-------------------
There are two possibilites:

1) Load it into an external viewer, which provides stretching.

2) Select a very high resoultion ;)

I didn't find a way to do this with G4C - but maybe there's a
possibilty...just wait for future versions...;)

SHOWGUI CAN'T LOAD A PICTURE
----------------------------
If ShowGUI cannot load a picture, it may be, that the picture
is in a different BIT depth than your screen can offer.
So, if you have a 16BIT screen and load in a 24BIT pic - it's
a problem! Also, if a pic eats too much mem, G4C will complain
with a shell-requester!

